<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4769&amp;p=42255#p42255"><![CDATA[
The assembler looks specifically for the $FF00+ symbol, as if it's a different instruction.  So the $FF00 is more like an IX or IY than an address.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Fri Jan 23, 2009 5:38 am</p><hr />
